    "narrative": "The Austin Waves' offense is spearheaded today by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56), both of whom benefit immensely from a favorable matchup against Burke and McGreevy, respectively. **Gunnar Henderson** holds the highest score of the day, buoyed by a substantial +14% platoon edge and the optimal leadoff spot. Similarly, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** capitalizes on the same high-floor conditions, with his dynamic platoon and favorable batting order making him a core contributor. In the outfield, **Jackson Merrill** (70.83) serves as an intriguing high-upside play; while his raw base is moderate, his aggressive usage against Keller\u2014combined with a slow delivery that boosts his SB potential by 2%\u2014makes him a critical asset in our quest to win the scarcest category. **Kyle Tucker** (64.03) and **Josh Lowe** (62.99) also remain locked in as strong starts, with **Josh Lowe** specifically benefiting from a +14% platoon boost against Holmes.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench today involves **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.94), who came remarkably close to displacing **Luis Robert Jr.** (48.72) or **Andy Pages** (50.12). Despite **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** posting a superior xwOBA of 0.384, the sheer quality of Ohtani on the mound forced our hand; the 19% penalty applied to his SP Skill projection makes him a liability compared to the favorable platoon matchups presented to our starting outfielders. We are also monitoring the risk associated with **Luis Robert Jr.**, whose 15% platoon penalty against Nelson makes his starting status precarious. While **Liam Hicks** (52.07), **Drake Baldwin** (47.27), **Nolan Schanuel** (58.51), **Nasim Nunez** (64.95), **Jacob Wilson** (56.44), and **Jorge Polanco** (52.80) are all active, we are prioritizing high-efficiency matchups to preserve our game caps, keeping the likes of **Coby Mayo** (47.10) and **Miguel Vargas** (40.14) in reserve as emergency depth.",
